DTSTAMP:20260720T220812Z
DTSTART;VALUE=DATE:20260901
DTEND;VALUE=DATE:20260902
SUMMARY:Deadline: Reflection (All Disciplines)
DESCRIPTION:Reflection is a Pro Helvetia grant supporting collective mediat
 ion projects that use innovative formats to foster critical reflection on 
 artistic practice and cultural transformation\, across all supported disci
 plines (design\, literature\, music\, performing arts\, visual arts\, and 
 innovation and society). Open to collectives comprising at least two cultu
 ral practitioners (artists\, creatives\, cultural practitioners\, or art e
 ducators)\; solo projects are excluded. ELIGIBILITY: requires a connection
  to Switzerland (Swiss citizenship\, or permanent residency with regular a
 rtistic activity in Switzerland)\; not open to practitioners without a Swi
 ss connection. For international collaborations\, at least 50 percent of p
 ractitioners must be from Switzerland. AMOUNT: maximum CHF 25\,000\, and n
 o more than 50 percent of the total budget. Deadlines twice a year: 1 Marc
 h (23:59 CET) and 1 September (23:59 CEST). Apply via the Pro Helvetia por
 tal.\n\nOrganisation: Pro Helvetia (Swiss Arts Council)\nLocation: Collect
 ives of at least two cultural practitioners\; for international collaborat
 ions at least 50 percent must be from Switzerland.\nAward: Maximum CHF 25\
 ,000 (cannot exceed 50 percent of total budget). No application fee.\nDura
 tion: Collective mediation project fostering critical reflection\; deadlin
 es twice yearly (1 March and 1 September).\n\nMore: https://prohelvetia.ch
 /en/find-support/reflection?utm_source=artificialnouveaugrantdesk&utm_medi
 um=referral
URL:https://prohelvetia.ch/en/find-support/reflection?utm_source=artificial
 nouveaugrantdesk&utm_medium=referral
LOCATION:Collectives of at least two cultural practitioners\; for internati
 onal collaborations at least 50 percent must be from Switzerland.
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:transmediale-pro-helvetia-digital-art-residency-2027@artificialnouveau.
 github.io
DTSTAMP:20260720T220812Z
DTSTART;VALUE=DATE:20260828
DTEND;VALUE=DATE:20260829
SUMMARY:Deadline: transmediale x Pro Helvetia Digital Art Residency 2027
DESCRIPTION:Fifth iteration of transmediale's Digital Art Residency\, in co
 operation with the Swiss Arts Council Pro Helvetia\, awarded to one indivi
 dual or collective working in digital art practices at the intersection of
  media arts\, performance\, sound and moving image. The two-month residenc
 y comes with an artist fee of CHF 2\,000 per month\, a CHF 15\,000 product
 ion grant to develop a new work or continue an existing project (open to a
 ll formats\, building on the residency research)\, and travel and accommod
 ation for the festival and residency\; the project must be completed by De
 cember 2027. The 2027 programme (transmediale's 40th anniversary\, themed 
 'RFC 40' after the early-internet Request for Comments documents) seeks pr
 oposals offering alternatives to how we understand\, respond to and shape 
 our technological conditions\, moving from critique to construction outsid
 e extractive logics. ELIGIBILITY: applicants must have Swiss nationality o
 r permanent residence in Switzerland\, be firmly established in the Swiss 
 cultural scene\, and meet Pro Helvetia's general requirements\; duos and c
 ollectives welcome (fee and grant shared). Deadline: 28 August 2026\, 23:5
 9 CEST.\n\nOrganisation: transmediale (in cooperation with the Swiss Arts 
 Council Pro Helvetia)\nLocation: Berlin\, Germany (two-month residency aro
 und the transmediale festival)\; applicants must be Swiss or Switzerland-b
 ased\nAward: Two-month residency with an artist fee of CHF 2\,000 per mont
 h\, plus a CHF 15\,000 production grant for the selected project\, and tra
 vel and accommodation for the festival and residency. For duos or collecti
 ves the fee and grant remain the same and are shared. No application fee.\
 nDuration: Two-month residency\; selected project must be completed by Dec
 ember 2027\n\nMore: https://transmediale.de/en/news/digital-art-residency-
 2027?utm_source=artificialnouveaugrantdesk&utm_medium=referral
URL:https://transmediale.de/en/news/digital-art-residency-2027?utm_source=a
 rtificialnouveaugrantdesk&utm_medium=referral
LOCATION:Berlin\, Germany (two-month residency around the transmediale fest
 ival)\; applicants must be Swiss or Switzerland-based
END:VEVENT
